column16: Our house is inspired by our experiences traveling and living around the world, blending the comforts of home with the welcoming international communities of our favorite hostels. We feel very fortunate that all of our guests share the same enthusiasm for life! We are a great option for travelers looking for something local and authentic. THE HOUSE:  Our house is a large three-level home built in the late 1930s with hardwood floors, skylights, large picture windows, gardens, and a backyard filled with trees and wildlife. column14: It's a short walk to Broadway and just a bit longer to downtown. 15th Ave, 3 blocks away, has many trendy cafes and restaurants.  Seattle has some of the best restaurants in the country. column15: BY BUS:  We are a quick walk from major bus lines that will take you downtown, north towards the University of Washington and Fremont (48), and south towards Tacoma. A few minutes¡¯ bus ride will take you to the Montlake-Lake Washington stop, a major hub for buses heading east towards Bellevue and Redmond and West towards South Lake Union.  BY CAR:  We are a few minutes from from the I5 and 520 expressways, which makes it easy to get to different areas of Seattle quickly. Because of our proximity to Broadway¡¯s hub of nightlife and shopping, a Lyft or Uber is usually only minutes away. If you¡¯re new to either ride-share program, we have promotional codes posted on our front wall! BY BIKE: LimeBike is a bike-sharing program that you rent using an app on your phone. Look for the bright green bikes around the city! If you have your own bike, we have bike racks, a repair kit, and a pump available for use in our garage. column16: The Lite Rail runs 3 minutes trips to downtown from 3 blocks away every 6 to 15 minutes for very cheap rates. Bus lines run on every major street. Uber and Lyft cover all of Seattle. Taxis are always running on broadway/pine/pike/downtown. "ORCA" Cards can be loaded with cash for quick bus payment via online or at a train station. Busses also accept cash and change. Should you decide to walk, it takes five to ten minutes to get to most any restaurant or bar in the neighborhood, 20 minutes to get downtown or to the convention center, 20 minutes to the Pike Place Market, and about 30 minutes to get to Lake Union, should you want to go sailing.

column15:
Welcome, my name is Dario.

I was born in Sicily and I moved to Seattle eight years ago. I am an Italian teacher and the director of Boys Tribe Project, an after school program to help boys develop emotional intelligence, learn how to play rough without hurting each other, and be creative with imaginative play and storytelling.

I love to cook Italian homemade food, traveling, personal growth, psychology, jazz and blues, foreign movies, interior design, modern dance, storytelling, art, and culture in general. I love hosting people, I used to host couch surfers and I also was traveling for a few years. The thing I like the most is to hear and to share stories from people all over the world.
